room -- t20. The Development of Online Learning in the Basic Course in Communication -- t21. Service Learning and Innovative Pedagogies -- t22. Out-of-Classroom Interactions Between Teachers and Students: Advising, Tutoring, Mentoring, and Coaching -- t23 Critical Communication Pedagogy -- tTeaching and Learning Communication Across the Lifespan -- t24. Meeting Children Where They Are: Adaptive Contingency Builds Early Communication Skills -- t25. Teaching Communication to School Children and Adolescents -- t26. Teaching Communication to College and University Students: The Basic Course in Higher Education -- t27. Teaching Communication to Working Adults -- t28. Assessment of College-Level Communication Programs -- tFuture Directions -- t29. The Future of Communication and Learning Research: Challenges, Opportunities, and Predictions -- tBiographical sketches -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn this volume, leading scholars from the fields of communication, educational psychology, and international education address what is known about the strategic role of interpersonal communication in the teaching/learning process. Instruction often involves spoken communication that carries information from teacher to learner, and in these instances the teacher's skillful and strategic use of language has a measurable impact on learning outcomes. Thus, the cumulative findings of instructional communication research are instrumental in maximizing the efficiency and effectiveness of both teaching and learning. Major sections of this volume include: Historical and Theoretical Foundations Instructor Characteristics and Behaviors Student Characteristics and Outcomes Pedagogy and Classroom Management Teaching and Learning Communication Across the Life-span This handbook serves researchers, professors, and graduate students by surveying the collective findings of research and experience concerning the intentional activity of teaching and learning.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Communication Studies.2bisacsh  aCommunication, Instruction, Teaching, Learning.1 aAtkinson, Jordan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAvtgis, Theodore A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBacklund, Phil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeebe, Steven A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBergen, Karla Mason, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBooth-Butterfield, Melanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrummernhenrich, Benjamin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCayanus, Jacob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCobley, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFassett, Deanna L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinn, Amber N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFloyd, Kory, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrei, Seth S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrymier, Ann Bainbridge, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldman, Zachary W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGolinkoff, Roberta Michnick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodboy, Alan K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodnight, Lisa J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHess, Jon A., econtributor.4ctb